The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | City team to play IPL opener
                                                City team to play IPL opener
                      
	Mumbai: The opening Twenty20 encounter in the BCCI-promoted Indian Premier League (IPL) will see liquor baron Vijay Mallyas Bangalore outfit take on Bollywood star Shah Rukh Khans Calcutta side at the M. Chinnaswamy Stadium under lights on April 18.         
	The final of the multi-million dollar league, as well as the two semi-finals, would be held in Mumbai  and in all probability at the Brabourne , Lalit Modi, IPL commissioner and chairman, said on Friday.         
	The final will be on June 1 and the semi-finals on May 30 and 31, all in Mumbai. We have the option of hosting these matches either at the CCI or DY Patil Stadium (in Navi Mumbai). I guess they will choose CCI, Modi said.         
	The IPL governing council had a day-long meeting on Friday with the eight franchise owners and representatives of the match staging associations. (PTI)                                                                                                                        
